        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XSecure_AesPerformOperationAndZeroizeKey</definition>
        <argsstring>(XSecure_ClientInstance *InstancePtr, u64 KeyAddr, const XSecure_AesDataBlockParams *AesDataParams)</argsstring>
        <name>XSecure_AesPerformOperationAndZeroizeKey</name>
        <param>
          <type>XSecure_ClientInstance *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u64</type>
          <declname>KeyAddr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="struct_x_secure___aes_data_block_params" kindref="compound">XSecure_AesDataBlockParams</ref> *</type>
          <declname>AesDataParams</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function calls IPI request to perform below operation: </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><verbatim>            - Write key into the key source provided by the user
            - Encrypt/decrypt a single block of data using the provided key
            - Zeroize the key once the AES operation is done
</verbatim></para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the XSecure_ClientInstance </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>KeyAddr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Address of the key to be used for AES operation </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>AesDataParams</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_secure___aes_data_block_params" kindref="compound">XSecure_AesDataBlockParams</ref> structure variable</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS On success</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE On failure </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Fill IPI Payload</para></listitem><listitem><para>Send an IPI request to the PLM by using the CDO command to call XSecure_AesOpNZeroizeKey API and returns the status of the IPI response.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>        </inbodydescription>
